  <body>
  
    <section name="Create hadoop jar">

      <p>This command allow to create a jar file that contains all the plugins and dependencies needed to run your analysis in distributed mode.</p>  

      <ul>
         <li><b>Optional parameters</b>: none</li>
	<br/>
        <li><b>Usage</b>:
<source>
$ eoulsan.sh createdesign [options] fastq_files fasta_file gff_gfile
</source>

</li>
        
       </ul>
      
    </section>

   <section name="Run manualy Eoulsan in Hadoop mode">

     <p>With the jar file generated your can manualy launch Eoulsan with a Hadoop command:</p>

<source>
$ hadoop -jar eoulsan-1.0-a19e9799.jar hdfs://toto.example.com/test/param.xml hdfs://toto.example.com/test/design.txt hdfs://toto.example.com/test
</source>

   </section>

  </body>
  
